  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-DOC-06, remove the always-open vertical `FilterPanel` sidebar and move existing filters into the command bar as compact dropdown buttons: Associated Only · File Type · Date Range · Threshold · Mode (Tags filter is FR-DOC-05, task 042 — already shipped). **BINDING**: preserve the `AssociatedOnly` auto-search behavior at `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` lines 359-375 VERBATIM when the toggle moves to the command bar. No "Filter Drawer" escape hatch in v1 (per §14 Q6 resolution). All 5 filters must function identically to today; AssociatedOnly toggle still auto-triggers re-search; sidebar `FilterPanel.tsx` is removed (or hidden when bound to the new layout).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer with PCF refactoring expertise. Familiar with Semantic Search PCF filter state, the existing `FilterPanel.tsx` sidebar, the `AssociatedOnly` auto-search hook at lines 359-375 of `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`, and Fluent UI v9 command-bar/dropdown patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` command bar hosts 5 compact dropdown buttons (Associated Only · File Type · Date Range · Threshold · Mode) + the Tags filter from task 042 + the view toggle from task 041. `FilterPanel.tsx` either removed entirely or hidden behind a feature flag for safe rollback. AssociatedOnly auto-search behavior preserved verbatim (same `useEffect` deps, same trigger logic). All 5 filters retain identical behavior. PCF builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DOC-06 completes the command-bar consolidation started by FR-DOC-04 (view toggle, task 041) and FR-DOC-05 (Tags filter, task 042). The sidebar `FilterPanel.tsx` becomes obsolete once all filters move to the bar. The **CRITICAL** binding constraint is that the `AssociatedOnly` toggle currently auto-triggers a re-search via a `useEffect` (lines 359-375) — this behavior MUST be preserved bit-for-bit when the toggle moves to the bar. Owner Clarifications (row 8) ruled out a "Filter Drawer" escape hatch — command-bar dropdowns are sufficient.
    </background>
