  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">Verify context &lt; 60%. If higher, run `context-handoff` before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="0.5" name="Invoke fluent-v9-component">Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` (binding per design.md §6.0). Load `fluent-v9-component-authoring.md`, `fluent-v9-theming.md`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Load knowledge">Read ADR-006, ADR-021, ADR-022, ADR-028; PCF CLAUDE.md. Read `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` carefully — locate lines 359-375 (AssociatedOnly `useEffect`) and document its deps + body in a comment. Read `FilterPanel.tsx` to inventory all 5 filter controls (Associated Only / File Type / Date Range / Threshold / Mode) and their state hooks.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Map filter controls to command bar">Plan command-bar layout (left → right): Associated Only `Switch` · File Type `Menu` · Date Range `Menu` · Threshold `Menu` · Mode `Menu` · Tags `TagFilter` (from task 042) · *spacer* · view toggle (from task 041). Verify horizontal layout fits at 1024 px minimum (NFR-03).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement Associated Only Switch in command bar">Add a Fluent v9 `Switch` to the command bar bound to the existing `associatedOnly` state. CRITICAL: do NOT touch the `useEffect` at lines 359-375 — leave it bit-identical. The Switch becomes the new visible trigger; the underlying state hook is unchanged.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement File Type dropdown">Add a Fluent v9 `Menu` to the command bar bound to the existing File Type state. Same options, same default, same filter semantics as the sidebar version.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Date Range dropdown">Add a Fluent v9 `Menu` to the command bar bound to the existing Date Range state. Same option set + default + filter semantics.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Implement Threshold dropdown">Add a Fluent v9 `Menu` to the command bar bound to the existing Threshold state. Same options.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Implement Mode dropdown">Add a Fluent v9 `Menu` to the command bar bound to the existing Mode state. Same options.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Remove FilterPanel sidebar">In `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`, remove the `&lt;FilterPanel /&gt;` JSX rendering. Either delete `FilterPanel.tsx` entirely OR keep the file but render nothing (feature-flag for safe rollback — preferred for v1). Adjust the parent grid/flex layout so the results area expands to fill the freed width.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify AssociatedOnly auto-search verbatim">Run a search, toggle the new command-bar Switch — verify the re-search auto-triggers identically to the sidebar version. Confirm `useEffect` lines 359-375 are byte-identical (diff against pre-change state).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Verify all 5 filters behave identically">For each filter (Associated Only / File Type / Date Range / Threshold / Mode), exercise the same scenarios as the sidebar version — verify identical results.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Dark-mode + a11y check">Run PCF in dev harness with `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`. Verify all command-bar dropdowns render with v9 tokens. Run axe scan in both themes.</step>
    <step order="12" name="1024 px viewport check">Resize browser to 1024 px width — verify command bar does NOT overflow horizontally, does NOT wrap, does NOT degrade text below 12 px (NFR-03).</step>
    <step order="13" name="Build verification">Run `npm run build:prod` from PCF root. Verify clean build.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">Invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check`. Resolve all findings. Verify `code-review` flags any change to the AssociatedOnly `useEffect` deps (binding constraint).</step>
    <step order="14" name="Checkpoint">Run `context-handoff` (silent: ✅ Checkpoint).</step>
    <step order="15" name="Update task tracking">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 043 status 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task (044).</step>
  </steps>

